---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Coordination Policy"
  description="General coordination principles for researchers and stakeholders."
  canonicalPath="/legal/coordination"
>
  <article class="prose-shell card mx-auto max-w-4xl p-8">
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-bold text-text">Coordination Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-text-soft">Effective: February 2026</p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-sm">
      Del Security follows structured coordination practices with stakeholders.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl">Good-faith reporting</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
      We support good-faith vulnerability reporting with reproducible technical details and clear authorization.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl">Coordination</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
      Timeline and embargo options can be coordinated case-by-case to balance remediation readiness and public risk.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl">Limitations</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
      We do not support processes tied to unauthorized access, coercive demands, or abusive exploitation.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl">Communication</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
      Status milestones are shared during active coordination. Timing depends on technical complexity and stakeholder engagement responsiveness.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
